e.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
MORTAL... And extremely lucky!<br>
<br>
Height: 5' when ready to pounce<br>
Age: Old enough to speak with dignity, but young enough <br>
to wrestle without it <br>
Occupation: Traveling personal trainer, specializing in the fine<br>
art of demonstration without action<br>
<br>
Xantho is the supreme force acting upon anything within the span of her arms. Her specialty lies in creating the impression of power, but it is foolish to assume anything but that every sure movement is backed by knowledge of fifty more dangerous. An agile mind makes Xantho's motions look choreographed, but anticipation of her next move will rarely prove useful. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Personal History</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Xantho is the sixth child of merchant parents. Raised in Sparta, she rarely missed an opportunity to watch combatants in training, in action, or posing for each other's benefit. When she was eleven, she was caught spying in a private training arena and was chastised by the authorities. As a last resort, her parents arranged private (and secret) tutoring in the fighting arts for Xantho under an ex-soldier. Their hope was that his intense and brutish regime would wipe from Xantho any desire to fight. They were wrong.<br>
<br>
Xantho now travels the lands surrounding the Mediterranean. When she is hungry, she offers her service as a trainer to the women who seek out her skills. When she can provide her own food and shelter, she studies those around her. In the motion of her charcoal she interprets the attitudes, actions, histories and desires of those she observes. In a 20-stroke sketch she can find the weakness of a future opponent or the specialties of a future lover.<br>
<br>
Desiring to understand what she saw in the faces of mothers, Xantho had one child, a daughter. They grew together through her first twenty years, then parted as friends. When last Xantho heard, her daughter was in the company of Amazons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.showPrevMessage?topicID=99.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.showNextMessage?topicID=99.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.emailToFriend?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.threadControl?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm33.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=99.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><t